console
    Use a console cable from PC â†’ device console port.
    PC > Desktop > Terminal (9600/8/none/1)

access privileged exec mode:
    <switchHostName>enable
    <switchHostName>#

access global config mode:
    <switchHostName>#conf t
    <switchHostName>(config)#

------------------------------------------------------------
configure banner message of the day:
------------------------------------------------------------
    <return>
    <switchHostName>enable
    <switchHostName>#conf t
    <switchHostName>(config)#banner motd #text message here#
        (# is just a delimiter, can be any symbol)

------------------------------------------------------------
access console configuration mode:
------------------------------------------------------------
    <switchHostName>(config)#line console 0

------------------------------------------------------------
configure IP address on an interface:
------------------------------------------------------------
    <return>
    <switchHostName>enable
    <switchHostName>#conf t
    <switchHostName>(config)#interface <g0/0/0>   (example)
    <switchHostName>(config-if)#ip address <IP> <MASK>
    <switchHostName>(config-if)#no shutdown

------------------------------------------------------------
configure privileged EXEC mode password:
------------------------------------------------------------
    <return>
    <switchHostName>enable
    <switchHostName>#conf t
    <switchHostName>(config)#enable secret <password>

------------------------------------------------------------
configure console password:
------------------------------------------------------------
    <return>
    <switchHostName>enable
    <switchHostName>#conf t
    <switchHostName>(config)#line console 0
    <switchHostName>(config-line)#password <password>

console connection will ask for a password @ login:
    <switchHostName>enable
    <switchHostName>#conf t
    <switchHostName>(config)#line console 0
    <switchHostName>(config-line)#login

------------------------------------------------------------
set domain address:
------------------------------------------------------------
    <return>
    <switchHostName>enable
    <switchHostName>#conf t
    <switchHostName>(config)#ip domain-name <domain.com>

------------------------------------------------------------
generate RSA key with 1024-bit length:
------------------------------------------------------------
    <return>
    <switchHostName>enable
    <switchHostName>#conf t
    <switchHostName>(config)#crypto key generate rsa
        1024

------------------------------------------------------------
create user with username "_" and secret "_" password:
------------------------------------------------------------
    <return>
    <switchHostName>enable
    <switchHostName>#conf t
    <switchHostName>(config)#username <user> secret <password>
        (example: username sshuser secret cisco123)

------------------------------------------------------------
enable SSH on VTY lines:
------------------------------------------------------------
    <return>
    <switchHostName>enable
    <switchHostName>#conf t
    <switchHostName>(config)#line vty 0 4
    <switchHostName>(config-line)#login local
    <switchHostName>(config-line)#transport input ssh

------------------------------------------------------------
encrypt all passwords:
------------------------------------------------------------
    <switchHostName>enable
    <switchHostName>#conf t
    <switchHostName>(config)#service password-encryption

------------------------------------------------------------
configure switch management VLAN IP (SVI):
------------------------------------------------------------
    <switchHostName>enable
    <switchHostName>#conf t
    <switchHostName>(config)#interface vlan 1   (or assigned mgmt VLAN)
    <switchHostName>(config-if)#ip address <IP> <MASK>
    <switchHostName>(config-if)#no shutdown

configure switch default gateway:
    <switchHostName>(config)#ip default-gateway <gateway-IP>

------------------------------------------------------------
verify settings:
------------------------------------------------------------
    show run
    show ip interface brief
    show interfaces status
    show vlan brief
    show arp
    show version
    show ip route

------------------------------------------------------------
save configuration:
------------------------------------------------------------
    copy run start

------------------------------------------------------------
FROM PC: secure remote session:
------------------------------------------------------------
    C:\> ssh -l <SSHuser> <router/switch IP>

    (example)
    C:\> ssh -l sshuser 192.168.1.1

------------------------------------------------------------
PC network testing:
------------------------------------------------------------
    C:\> ipconfig
    C:\> ping <IP>
    C:\> tracert <IP>
